            {
              "id": "app.opengrep-rules.javascript.lang.security.audit.detect-non-literal-regexp",
              "name": "app.opengrep-rules.javascript.lang.security.audit.detect-non-literal-regexp",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "app.opengrep-rules.javascript.lang.security.audit.detect-non-literal-regexp"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "RegExp() called with a `name` function argument, this might allow an attacker to cause a Regular Expression Denial-of-Service (ReDoS) within your application as RegExP blocks the main thread. For this reason, it is recommended to use hardcoded regexes instead. If your regex is run on user-controlled input, consider performing input validation or use a regex checking/sanitization library such as https://www.npmjs.com/package/recheck to verify that the regex does not appear vulnerable to ReDoS."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "RegExp() called with a `name` function argument, this might allow an attacker to cause a Regular Expression Denial-of-Service (ReDoS) within your application as RegExP blocks the main thread. For this reason, it is recommended to use hardcoded regexes instead. If your regex is run on user-controlled input, consider performing input validation or use a regex checking/sanitization library such as https://www.npmjs.com/package/recheck to verify that the regex does not appear vulnerable to ReDoS."
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CWE-1333: Inefficient Regular Expression Complexity",
                  "A05:2021 - Security Misconfiguration",
                  "A06:2017 - Security Misconfiguration"
                ],
                "cwe": [
                  "CWE-1333: Inefficient Regular Expression Complexity"
                ],
                "owasp": [
                  "A05:2021 - Security Misconfiguration",
                  "A06:2017 - Security Misconfiguration"
                ],
                "security-severity": "3.0"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/Regular_expression_Denial_of_Service_-_ReDoS"
            },
            {
              "id": "app.opengrep-rules.javascript.lang.best-practice.lazy-load-module",
              "name": "app.opengrep-rules.javascript.lang.best-practice.lazy-load-module",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "app.opengrep-rules.javascript.lang.best-practice.lazy-load-module"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Lazy loading can complicate code bundling if care is not taken, also `require`s are run synchronously by Node.js. If they are called from within a function, it may block other requests from being handled at a more critical time. The best practice is to `require` modules at the beginning of each file, before and outside of any functions."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Lazy loading can complicate code bundling if care is not taken, also `require`s are run synchronously by Node.js. If they are called from within a function, it may block other requests from being handled at a more critical time. The best practice is to `require` modules at the beginning of each file, before and outside of any functions."
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": [],
                "security-severity": "3.0"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://nodesecroadmap.fyi/chapter-2/dynamism.html"
            },
